1
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:03,040
WOMAN: (AMERICAN SOUTH ACCENT)
When I was a child,

2
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:07,480
my favourite story was
about a man who lived forever,

3
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:11,560
but whose eyes were heavy
with the weight of all he'd seen.

4
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:14,120
A man who fell from the stars.

5
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:16,720
(BEEPING)

6
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,400
I knew you'd find me eventually.

7
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,080
GUNSLINGER:
Make peace with your gods.

8
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:34,080
Once they were your gods, too.

9
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:35,600
Not any more.

10
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:40,440
(PANTING)

11
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:50,080
(GROANING)

12
00:00:57,720 --> 00:00:59,960
Am I... Am I the last one?

13
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:02,120
There's one more.

14
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:05,000
The doctor.

15
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,160
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

16
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:49,320
DOCTOR: "Mercy. 81 residents.”

17
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:55,680
Look at this,
it's a load of stones and lumps of wood.

18
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,120
(WHIRRING)

19
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,520
AMY: What is it?

20
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,320
A load of stones and lumps of wood.

21
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,720
RORY: Uh, the sign does say "Keep Out”.

22
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:17,680
I see "Keep Out” signs as suggestions
more than actual orders.

23
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,600
Like "Dry-Clean Only".

24
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:46,160
(CRACKLES)

25
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,720
That's not right.

26
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,040
(WHIRRING)

27
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:56,680
It's a street lamp.

28
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,600
An electric street lamp,
about 10 years too early.

29
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,320
-It's only a few years out.
-That's what you said

30
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,880
when you left your phone charger
in Henry VIII's ensuite.

31
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,440
Doctor, um...

32
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:09,360
Anachronistic electricity,
"Keep Out" signs, aggressive stares,

33
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:12,040
has someone been peeking
at my Christmas list?

34
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,320
Doctor...

35
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:22,360
(PATRONS CHATTING)

36
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,760
Tea.

37
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,360
But the strong stuff.

38
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,080
Leave the bag in.

39
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:46,120
What you doing here, son?

40
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,640
Son? (CHUCKLES)

41
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,440
-You can stay.
-Sir?

42
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,720
Might I enquire who you is?

43
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:54,720
Of course. I'm the Doctor, this is...

44
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:57,120
No need to stand. You see that?

45
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,320
Manners.

46
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:02,000
Oh, thank you,
but I don't need a new suit.

47
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,520
I'm the undertaker, sir.

48
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,320
(MEN LAUGHING)

49
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,840
I got a question.

50
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,360
Is you an alien?

51
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:14,480
Well, um... Bit personal.
It's all relative, isn't it?

52
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:18,240
I mean, I think you're the aliens.
But in this context, yes.

53
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,560
Yes, I suppose I am.

54
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,560
(ALL CLAMOURING)

55
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,800
-AMY: (SCREAMS) Doctor!
-Guys.

56
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:27,400
AMY: Put him down!
WOMAN: Don't think we won't kill you!

57
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,560
RORY: Leave her alone!

58
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,520
Don't worry, everything is
completely under control.

59
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,360
RORY: Get off me!
DOCTOR: Guys, guys...

60
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,480
DOCTOR: Guys, guys... Oh, okay.

61
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,560
-(SHOUTING)
-MAN: Get out!

62
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,320
Ah!

63
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:44,160
Ow! (BONES CRACKING)

64
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,320
(GUNS COCKING)

65
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,480
Oh.

66
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,400
He's coming.

67
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,640
Oh, God! He's coming!

68
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:58,720
Preacher, say something.

69
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,960
Our Father, who art in Heaven,

70
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,160
hallowed be Thy name.

71
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,000
-Thy Kingdom come...
-(SHUDDERING)

72
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:16,040
"Thy will be done..."

73
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,160
(GUNSHOT)

74
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:21,600
You, bow tie,

75
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,520
get back across that line.

76
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,680
Now.

77
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,160
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

78
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,400
(EXHALES)

79
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,600
Isaac, he said he was a doctor.

80
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,360
An alien doctor.

81
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,960
Is that a reason
to hand him to his death?

82
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,240
But, Isaac, it could be him.

83
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,720
You know it ain't.

84
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:00,960
Ma'am.

85
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,600
MAN: Just let him go like that?

86
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,880
He's seen you, boy.

87
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,480
-What was that outside?
-The Gunslinger.

88
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,880
Showed up three weeks back.

89
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:21,520
We've been prisoners ever since.

90
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,760
See that borderline
stretching round the town?

91
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,680
Woke up one morning, there it was.

92
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,480
Nothing gets past it, in or out.

93
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:31,080
No supply wagons, no reinforcements.

94
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,680
Pretty soon the whole town's
going to starve to death.

95
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,840
But he let us in.

96
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:38,360
You ain't carrying any food.
Just three more mouths to feed.

97
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,560
We'll all die even sooner now.

98
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,200
What happens if someone
crosses the line?

99
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,520
Ah, well,
he wasn't a very good shot, then.

100
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,360
He was aiming for the hat.

101
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,160
He shoots people's hats?

102
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,560
I think it was a warning shot.

103
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:56,760
Ah, no. Yes. I see. Hmm...

104
00:06:56,840 --> 00:07:00,080
What does he want?
Has he issued some kind of demand?

105
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:02,640
Says he wants us to give him
"the alien doctor”.

106
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:05,600
But that's you.
Why would he want to kill you?

107
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:08,360
-Unless he's met you.
-And how could he know we'd be here?

108
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:10,240
We didn't even know we'd be here.

109
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,640
(CHUCKLES) We were aiming for Mexico.

110
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:15,600
The Doctor was taking us to see
the Day of the Dead Festival.

111
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,440
-(SIZZLING)
-ISAAC: Mexico's 200 miles due south.

112
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:22,240
Well, that's what happens when people
get toast crumbs on the console.

113
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,840
Anyway, I think it's about time
I met him, don't you?

114
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,640
Who?

115
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,600
The chap outside said
I could be the alien doctor

116
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:31,240
but you said I wasn't,
so you already know who it is.

117
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:34,400
(CHUCKLES) Two alien doctors.
We're like buses.

118
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:37,840
Resident 81, I presume,
so beloved by the townsfolk

119
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,680
he warranted an alteration to the sign.

120
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,520
Probably because he'd rigged up
these electrics.

121
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,000
And I'm guessing he's in here,

122
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,680
because if half the town suddenly
wanted to throw me to my death,

123
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,800
this is where I'd want to be.

124
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:50,000
-I don't know what you...
-MAN: It's all right, Isaac.

125
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,240
I think the time for subterfuge
has passed.

126
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,240
Good afternoon.

127
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,360
My name is Kahler-Jex.

128
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,320
I'm the doctor.

129
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,560
The Kahler, I love the Kahler.

130
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,720
They're one of the most ingenious races
in the galaxy.

131
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,840
Seriously.

132
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:26,360
They could build a spaceship
out of Tupperware and moss.

133
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:28,360
All right. How did you get here?

134
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:31,920
My craft crashed about a mile or so
out of town.

135
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,600
I would have died
if Isaac and the others

136
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,480
hadn't pulled me from the wreckage.

137
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:37,720
And you stayed as their doctor?

138
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:40,840
On my world I was a surgeon,
so it seemed logical.

139
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:44,000
And it gave me an opportunity
to repay my debt to them.

140
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,680
(SCOFFS) Listen to him.

141
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:47,640
Talking like it was nothing.

142
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,160
Tell 'em about the cholera.

143
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,240
Now, Isaac, I'm sure our guests...

144
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:54,120
ISAAC: Two years after he arrived,
there was an outbreak of cholera.

145
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,640
Thanks to the doc here,
not a single person died.

146
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:59,400
A minor infection we'd found
a treatment for centuries ago.

147
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:03,320
No, no, no, what do you call them,
the electrics?

148
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,040
Using my ship as a generator,

149
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,680
I was able to rig up some rudimentary
heating and lighting for the town.

150
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,440
So, why does the Gunslinger want you?

151
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,040
-It don't matter.
-I'm just saying, if we knew that...

152
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,000
ISAAC: America's the land
of second chances.

153
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:19,360
We call this town Mercy for a reason.

154
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:22,080
Though there's some round here
don't feel that way.

155
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,880
Now, Isaac, we've discussed this...

156
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,600
People whose lives you've saved are
suddenly saying we should hand you over.

157
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,560
They're scared, that's all.

158
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:32,120
-You can hardly blame them.
-Them being scared scares me.

159
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,840
War only ended five years back.

160
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:40,920
That old violence
is still under the surface.

161
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,840
We give up Doc Jex, then we're handing
the keys to the town over to chaos.

162
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,600
Did you try to repair your craft?

163
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,200
Surely someone with your skills...

164
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,640
It really was very badly damaged.

165
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,720
We evacuate the town,

166
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,640
our ship's just over the hills,
room for everyone.

167
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,640
I'll pop out and bring it back here,
Robert's your uncle.

168
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,080
Really? Simple as that?

169
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:06,400
-No crazy schemes, no negotiations?
-I've matured. I'm 1200 years old now.

170
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,840
Plus, I don't want to miss The Archers.

171
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:10,240
Oh, so you're not even
a tiny bit curious?

172
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:13,400
Why would I be curious?
It's a mysterious space-cowboy assassin.

173
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,920
Curious? Of course I'm not curious.

174
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,240
ISAAC: Son?

175
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:20,240
You still got to get past
the Gunslinger, how you gonna do that?

176
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,160
With a little sleight of hand.

177
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:34,080
-You okay?
-Yeah, fine, yeah. Keep moving.

178
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:37,400
Well, next time,
you get to wear Jex's clothes.

179
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,400
(HORSE SNORTING)

180
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,800
Can I borrow your horse, please?

181
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:59,760
It's official Marshal business.

182
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,800
He's called Joshua.

183
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:04,120
It's from the Bible.
It means "the deliverer".

184
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,720
-(HORSE SNORTING)
-No, he isn't.

185
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,960
-What?
-I speak horse, he's called Susan.

186
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,120
(SNORTS)

187
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,680
And he wants you to respect
his life choices.

188
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,280
-(NEIGHS)
-Hup!

189
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:34,120
I, uh... I think he's seen us.

190
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,520
This way!

191
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:45,120
When this is all done,
do you want us to take you home?

192
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,200
Thank you.

193
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:50,880
But I have already given
everything I have to the Kahler.

194
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,760
My skills, my energy.

195
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,880
All that was good in me.

196
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,400
(HORSES NEIGHING)

197
00:11:57,480 --> 00:12:00,520
But here, I could start afresh.

198
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,960
I could remember myself and help people.

199
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,960
That's all I ever wanted to do.

200
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,200
End suffering.

201
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,520
Here.

202
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:22,320
-You're a mother, aren't you?
-How did you know?

203
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,400
There's kindness in your eyes.

204
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,760
And sadness.

205
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:29,160
But a ferocity, too.

206
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,840
It wasn't exactly straightforward.

207
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,480
It seldom is.

208
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,920
And what about you? Are you a father?

209
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:41,920
Yes. In a way, I suppose I am.

210
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:01,240
So, we wait here till the Doctor
comes to pick us up in your ship.

211
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,960
Yes, I know.

212
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:04,880
I was there when we agreed it.

213
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:08,240
Yeah, I said that
more for my benefit than yours.

214
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:18,240
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
-(NEIGHS)

215
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:21,560
Yeah, I know we're in a hurry,
I just want to check something out.

216
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:27,120
Two ticks.
There's something niggling me.

217
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:30,560
-(SNORTS)
-Yes, yes, it could be important.

218
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:33,640
-(SNORTS)
-0i, don't swear.

219
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,640
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)

220
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,360
(SNIFFS)

221
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,160
(SNORTING)

222
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:10,560
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

223
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,880
(SNORTS)

224
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,360
Yes, I wear a Stetson now.

225
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,560
-(SNORTING)
-Yes, good point, Susan.

226
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,320
Where is the damage?

227
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,920
(BUZZING)

228
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:09,840
Ow.

229
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,920
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

230
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,120
(ALARM BLARING)

231
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,520
Ah!

232
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,400
(WHINNIES)

233
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:24,200
(ALARM ECHOING)

234
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,840
That's the alarm on my ship.

235
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:53,400
Maybe the Doctor wants to
get it working again.

236
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,640
But that wasn't the plan.

237
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,520
He's not following the plan.

238
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,360
Welcome to my world.

239
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,880
(GROANING)

240
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,480
COMPUTER: Security breach.

241
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:14,480
You have 10 seconds
to enter the pass code

242
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:17,280
or this vehicle will self-destruct.

243
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:20,360
Thank you for choosing
Abaraxas Security Software.

244
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:23,360
Incinerating intruders
for three centuries.

245
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:27,440
Nine, eight, seven...

246
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,920
Self-destruct overridden.

247
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,400
This is an awful lot of security
for a titchy spacecraft.

248
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,320
Awaiting command.

249
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,560
Tell me everything you can
about the Gunslinger.

250
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,280
-File not found.
-Ah!

251
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:42,520
Please choose from
technical specifications,

252
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:46,560
flight recorder, personal files,
maps and charts.

253
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,800
Personal files of Dr Kahler-Jex.

254
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:53,480
KAHLER-JEX: Names of diseased subjects
can be found on the drop-down menu.

255
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:58,520
(BEEPING, PEOPLE SCREAMING IN PAIN)

256
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:20,240
I'm sorry, Amy,
he really should have followed the plan.

257
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,080
(WHIRRING)

258
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:30,920
Don't shoot! Don't shoot. Don't shoot!

259
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:36,200
I know who you are.
And who Jex is, too.

260
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:43,800
Now, what I don't understand is
why you haven't just walked into town

261
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,400
and killed him.

262
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:47,640
People will get in the way.

263
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,680
Look, you want justice,
you deserve justice,

264
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:52,000
but this isn't the way.
We can put him on trial. We can...

265
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:55,880
When he starts killing your people,
you can use your justice.

266
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:03,240
Isaac says he doesn't care
about my past.

267
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:07,600
But things may have been uncovered
that even he might struggle to forgive.

268
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,720
So, it's best we beat a hasty retreat.

269
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:14,200
We? (STAMMERS) I'm coming with you?

270
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:17,280
It's unlikely the Gunslinger will shoot
if I'm with you.

271
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,920
As far as I can tell,

272
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:22,200
he's programmed to take innocent lives
only if absolutely necessary.

273
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,920
Oh, well, colour me reassured.

274
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:33,480
What are you doing?

275
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:38,200
No more warning shots.

276
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,920
I'll kill the next person
to step over that line.

277
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,840
Make sure it's Jex.

278
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:58,680
It was stupid of me. I realise that now.

279
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:01,320
I just thought I'd put you all
in enough danger.

280
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,800
-Perhaps if I left...
-He's lying.

281
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,520
Every word.

282
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:09,720
Everything he says,

283
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,240
it's all

284
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,280
lies.

285
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,400
This man is a murderer.

286
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,640
-I am a scientist!
-Sit down.

287
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:22,640
Sit down!

288
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:25,880
Tell them what you are.

289
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,440
What am I?

290
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,560
A war hero.

291
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,960
Okay.

292
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:37,760
Somebody want to tell me
what is going on?

293
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:40,000
The Gunslinger is a cyborg.

294
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:42,800
-A what?
-Half man, half machine.

295
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,480
A weapon.

296
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,680
Jex built it.
He and his team took volunteers,

297
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:49,360
told them they'd been selected
for special training,

298
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:51,360
then experimented on them,

299
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:55,000
fused their bodies with weaponry
and programmed them to kill.

300
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,320
Okay, why?

301
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:59,920
Why would you do that, doc?

302
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,600
We'd been at war for nine years.

303
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:06,000
A war that had already decimated
half of our planet.

304
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:10,400
Our task was to bring peace.
And we did.

305
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:16,040
We built an army that routed the enemy
and ended the war in less than a week.

306
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,600
Do you want me to repent?

307
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:20,360
To beg forgiveness
for saving millions of lives?

308
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,320
And how many died screaming
on the operating table

309
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,680
before you had found your advantage?

310
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,480
War is another world.

311
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:29,400
You cannot apply the politics of peace
to what I did,

312
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:32,200
to what any of us did.

313
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:34,520
But what happened then?
How come you're here?

314
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:39,120
KAHLER-JEX: When the war ended,
we had the cyborgs decommissioned.

315
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:42,480
One of them must have got
its circuitry damaged in battle.

316
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:45,920
It went offline and began
hunting down the team that created it,

317
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,280
until just two of us were left.

318
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:50,000
We fled.

319
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:53,800
And our ships crashed here.

320
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,200
So, what do we do with Jex?

321
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:09,520
-What do we do with him?
-Yeah, I mean, he's a war criminal.

322
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,960
No, he's the guy that saved the town
from cholera.

323
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,280
The guy that gave us heat and light.

324
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:16,040
Look, Jex may be a criminal
and, yeah, kind of creepy...

325
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,280
And still in the room.

326
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:19,840
...but I think we should put aside
what he did and find another solution.

327
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,280
RORY: Another solution? It's him or us.

328
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:23,040
When did we start
letting people get executed?

329
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:25,080
Did I miss a memo? Doctor, tell him.

330
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,240
Hmm?

331
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,320
Yes.

332
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:31,280
I don't know. Whatever Amy said.

333
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:35,280
KAHLER-JEX: Looking at you, Doctor,
is like looking into a mirror,

334
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,440
almost.

335
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:39,360
There's rage there, like me.

336
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,200
Guilt, like me.

337
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:42,960
Solitude.

338
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:46,400
Everything but the nerve to do
what needs to be done.

339
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:51,200
Thank the gods my people
weren't relying on you to save them.

340
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,480
No! No!

341
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:54,880
But these people are.

342
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,200
Out! Out! Out!

343
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:58,640
(GRUNTS)

344
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:03,200
Oh, you're really letting him do this?

345
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,120
Save us all? Yeah, I really am.

346
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:09,200
Move!

347
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,800
No, I...

348
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,080
-No.
-Move!

349
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:15,240
(STAMMERING)

350
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,720
WOMAN: Now what's going on?

351
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:25,560
Get over that line!

352
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:26,800
(GROANS)

353
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:30,440
Hey!

354
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,240
(GROANS)

355
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:37,720
You wouldn't.

356
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,440
I genuinely don't know.

357
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,240
ISAAC: Doctor?

358
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,480
Doctor?

359
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:52,680
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

360
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:54,480
Let him come back, Doctor.

361
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:58,160
Or what? You won't shoot me, Amy.

362
00:22:58,240 --> 00:23:00,560
How do you know? Maybe I've changed.

363
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:03,440
I mean, you've clearly been taking
stupid lessons since I saw you last...

364
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,560
(GUNSHOT)

365
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,600
-I didn't mean to do that.
-(GUNSHOT)

366
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:10,240
Everyone who isn't an American,
drop your gun.

367
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,560
We can end this right now.
We could save everyone right now!

368
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:16,640
This is not how we roll and you know it.
What's happened to you, Doctor?

369
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,280
When did killing someone
become an option?

370
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:20,560
-Jex has to answer for his crimes.
-And what then?

371
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:23,240
Are you going to hunt down everyone
who's made a gun or a bullet or a bomb?

372
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:24,440
But they keep coming back.
Don't you see?

373
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:26,280
Every time I negotiate,
I try to understand.

374
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:28,960
Well, not today. No.
Today I honour the victims first.

375
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:30,520
His, the Master's, the Daleks',

376
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:33,480
all the people who died
because of my mercy!

377
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:38,960
See, this is what happens
when you travel alone for too long.

378
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:42,080
Well, listen to me, Doctor,
we can't be like him.

379
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:44,400
We have to be better than him.

380
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:56,320
Amelia Pond.

381
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,520
(EXHALES)

382
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:04,440
Fine. Fine! We think of something else.

383
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,920
But frankly,
I'm betting on the Gunslinger.

384
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:10,120
(AIR CRACKLING IN DISTANCE)

385
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:12,360
Jex, move over the line.

386
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:14,800
Now!

387
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:31,960
Make peace with your gods.

388
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:36,920
Kahler-Tech, isn't it?
I remember all your names, even now.

389
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:41,000
Please, I'd never hurt anyone again.

390
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:44,080
I'm even helping people here.

391
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:48,440
Last chance. Make peace with your gods.

392
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:51,160
ISAAC: No!

393
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,000
(GROANING)

394
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:55,360
Isaac! Hey.

395
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:59,280
Isaac? Isaac! Isaac, it's okay.

396
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:06,120
It's okay. It's okay. We can get you
to Jex's surgery. He can save you.

397
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:09,320
Listen to me. You gotta stay.

398
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:12,840
You gotta look after everyone.

399
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:14,720
It won't come to that, Isaac.

400
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:18,400
Protect Jex. Protect my town.

401
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,520
You're both good men.

402
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:30,520
You just forget it sometimes.

403
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:04,080
Take Jex to a cell.

404
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:07,000
If anything happens to him,
you'll have me to answer to.

405
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:12,280
(GRUNTING)

406
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:18,560
-This has gone on long enough.
-You are right.

407
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:28,080
You've got until noon tomorrow.

408
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:33,560
Give him to me or I'll kill you all.

409
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:48,760
-Oh, my God, you're the Marshal.
-Yeah.

410
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,600
And you're the Deputy.

411
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:54,560
(BELL TOLLING)

412
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,720
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

413
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:05,040
Come in.

414
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:09,760
Marshal. Ma'am.

415
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:13,400
Fella.

416
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:15,520
-You need to come outside.
-Why? What's wrong?

417
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,960
Just come outside.

418
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:20,720
And you should put that on.

419
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:45,120
What's going on?

420
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,760
He in there?

421
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:58,320
Leave the keys and take a walk.

422
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,320
Time you get back, this'll all be done.

423
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,160
I promised Isaac I'd protect him.

424
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:06,680
Protecting him got Isaac dead.
Tomorrow, it's gonna get us all dead.

425
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:10,520
We thought Isaac was right to fight,
but it's different now.

426
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:15,720
We gotta say, "All right, we lost,"
and give that thing what it wants.

427
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,920
What it wants is to kill our friend.

428
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,000
We don't got any ill feeling
toward the doc.

429
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:23,040
We just thinking about our families.

430
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,040
Hand him over and we all safe again.

431
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:28,240
You know I can't do that.

432
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:31,080
Then we got us a problem.

433
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:39,120
-Please don't do this.
-Why?

434
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,800
-Reckon you're quicker than me?
-Almost certainly not.

435
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:45,800
But this, lynch mobs,
the town turning against itself,

436
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,800
this is everything Isaac didn't want.

437
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:56,800
-How old are you?
-Nearly 19.

438
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:58,560
That's 18, then.

439
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,920
You're too young
to have fought in the war,

440
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:02,520
so I'm guessing you've never
shot anyone before, have you?

441
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:05,960
-First time for everything.
-But that's how all this started.

442
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:08,440
Jex turned someone into a weapon.

443
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:11,800
Now that same story's
going to make you a killer, too.

444
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:14,280
Don't you see?
Violence doesn't end violence,

445
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,840
it extends it.

446
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:22,880
And I don't think you want to do this.

447
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:27,000
I don't think
you want to become that man.

448
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:33,000
-There's kids here.
-I know.

449
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:34,760
Who I can save if you'll let me.

450
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:39,720
-He really worth the risk?
-Don't know.

451
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:42,960
But you are.

452
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:49,600
(UNCOCKS GUN)

453
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:11,000
Frightened people.
Give me a Dalek any day.

454
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:30,120
Fresh coffee, Marshal.

455
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:36,480
For what it's worth,
I know you're going to save us.

456
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:39,280
Isaac made you Marshal for a reason.

457
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:42,320
And if you're good enough for him,
you're good enough for me.

458
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:44,560
Reckon you should know that.

459
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,240
Thank you.

460
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:55,040
(EXHALES)

461
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:58,560
Oi! Get out of it.

462
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,440
Let me guess,

463
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:07,640
the good folk of Mercy wanted me
to take a little stroll into the desert.

464
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:12,440
You could turn a blind eye.
No one would blame you.

465
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,560
You'd be a hero.

466
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,680
But I can't, can I?

467
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:20,880
Because then Isaac's death
would mean nothing,

468
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:24,120
just another casualty
in your endless bloody war.

469
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:29,080
Do you want me to hand you over?
Is that what you want?

470
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,280
Do you even know...

471
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:33,200
You think I'm unaffected by what I did?

472
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:36,640
That I don't hear them screaming
every time I close my eyes?

473
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:41,680
It would be so much simpler
if I was just one thing, wouldn't it?

474
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:45,040
The mad scientist
who made that killing machine

475
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:49,000
or the physician, who's dedicated
his life to serving this town.

476
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:51,600
The fact that I'm both bewilders you.

477
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,520
Oh, I know exactly what you are

478
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:56,760
and I see this reformation
for what it really is.

479
00:31:57,440 --> 00:32:00,520
You committed an atrocity
and chose this as your punishment.

480
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:02,360
Don't get me wrong, good choice.

481
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:05,160
Civilised hours, lots of adulation,
nice weather but...

482
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:07,280
But justice doesn't work like that!

483
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:10,840
You don't get to decide
when and how your debt is paid!

484
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:15,920
(EXHALES)

485
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,800
In my culture,

486
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:33,080
we believe that when you die,
your spirit has to climb a mountain

487
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:37,080
carrying the souls of everyone
you wronged in your lifetime.

488
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:41,840
Imagine the weight I will have to lift.

489
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:46,120
The monsters I created,

490
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:48,120
the people they killed,

491
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,360
Isaac.

492
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:52,480
He was my friend.

493
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:56,960
Now his soul will be in my arms, too.

494
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:01,520
Can you see now why I fear death?

495
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:12,680
You want to hand me over?
There's no shame in that.

496
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,640
But you won't.

497
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:21,000
We all carry our prisons with us.

498
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,440
Mine is my past.

499
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:29,760
Yours is your morality.

500
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:32,520
"We all carry our prisons with us.”

501
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:34,680
Ha!

502
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,720
(NECK CRACKING)

503
00:33:57,800 --> 00:33:59,600
(CLOCK HAND CREAKING)

504
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:06,280
Help me. Help me to keep...

505
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:08,480
(MURMURING PRAYERS, INDISTINCT)

506
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:19,440
(CLOCK TICKING)

507
00:34:25,640 --> 00:34:27,400
(AIR CRACKLING OUTSIDE)

508
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:45,040
(CLOCK CHIMING)

509
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:21,240
(GRUNTS)

510
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:22,960
(WHIRRING)

511
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,200
(SCREAMING)

512
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:44,720
Ready?

513
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:51,560
Ready?

514
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:23,040
(BEEPING)

515
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:28,160
Disengage. It's a trick.

516
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:31,480
(FOOTSTEPS CLANGING)

517
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,720
(WHISPERING) Save us, O Lord...

518
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:56,200
(ALL SCREAMING)

519
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:06,880
Uh...

520
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:13,200
Go! Just go.
I can't save them while you're here.

521
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,920
(WEAPON POWERING DOWN)

522
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:02,280
COMPUTER: Nine, eight, seven...

523
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:04,360
Self-destruct overridden.

524
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:05,480
(PANTING)

525
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:12,600
Deactivate automatic targeting.
Switch to manual.

526
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:34,800
Right.

527
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:38,720
-Where is he?
-He's gone.

528
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:41,440
-Where? Answer me/
-Away from here.

529
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:44,160
Look up. Any second now you'll see
the vapour trail of his ship.

530
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:47,200
This is their home,
not the backdrop for your revenge.

531
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:49,400
Go after him.
Take this battle away from...

532
00:38:49,480 --> 00:38:51,400
KAHLER-JEX: (ON PA) Kahler-Tech!

533
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:52,800
Kahler-Tech!

534
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:56,000
Jex! Coward!

535
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:58,400
-Where are you?
-I'm in my ship.

536
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:01,280
Jex, what're you doing? Just go!

537
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:02,520
KAHLER-JEX: Where are you from?

538
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,280
Where on Kahler?

539
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:07,480
Now? You're asking him this now?

540
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:10,160
-Gabrian.
-I know it.

541
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,720
It's beautiful there.

542
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,600
-When this is over, will you go back?
-How can I?

543
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,800
I'm a monster now.

544
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:19,800
So am 1.

545
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:22,240
Just go! Finish this!

546
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,160
I will find you.

547
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:27,560
If I have to tear this universe apart,

548
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:29,000
I will find you.

549
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:31,480
I don't doubt that.

550
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:35,200
You'll chase me to another planet,

551
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,240
and another race will be caught
in the crossfire.

552
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:40,280
Then face me!

553
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:43,760
COMPUTER: Countdown
to self-destruct resumed.

554
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:47,400
-Face me!
-No. You've killed enough.

555
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,800
I'm ending the war for you, too.

556
00:39:49,880 --> 00:39:52,600
COMPUTER: Countdown
to self-destruct resumed.

557
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:53,920
-What's going on?
-Ten...

558
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:56,280
The countdown. What's going on, Jex?

559
00:39:56,360 --> 00:40:00,520
Thank you, Doctor. I have to face
the souls of those I've wronged.

560
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:03,240
-COMPUTER: ...five, four...
-Perhaps they will be kind.

561
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:07,840
-...three, two, one, zero.
-(ALARM RINGING)

562
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:47,480
(SIGHS)

563
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:54,360
He behaved with honour at the end.

564
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,320
Maybe more than me.

565
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:02,880
We could take you back to your world.

566
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:07,760
You could help with the reconstruction.

567
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:11,480
I will walk into the desert
and self-destruct.

568
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:17,480
I'm a creature of war,
I have no role to play during peace.

569
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:23,120
Except, maybe, to protect it.

570
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:31,000
Okay, so, our next trip...

571
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:33,600
Oh! You know all the monkeys and dogs
they sent into space

572
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:34,840
in the '50s and '60s?

573
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:37,360
You will never guess
what really happened to them.

574
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:39,320
Um, could we leave it a while?

575
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,920
Our friends are going to start noticing
that we're ageing faster than them.

576
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,680
Another time. No worries.

577
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:51,480
(TARDIS DOOR CLOSES)

578
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:16,080
WOMAN: By the time
the Gunslinger arrived,

579
00:42:16,160 --> 00:42:20,320
the people of Mercy were used to
the strange and the impossible.

580
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:21,760
(WHOOSHING)

581
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:27,360
Where he came from didn't matter.

582
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:32,440
As a man once said,
America is a land of second chances.

583
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:40,760
Do I believe the story? I don't know.

584
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:44,920
My great-grandmother must have been
a little girl when he arrived.

585
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:47,400
But next time you're in Mercy,

586
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:49,760
ask someone
why they don't have a marshal

587
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:52,600
or sheriff or policeman there.

588
00:42:52,680 --> 00:42:56,000
"We've got our own arrangement, "
they'll say.

589
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:58,920
Then they'll smile
like they got a secret.

590
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:03,440
Like they got their own special angel
watching out for 'em,

591
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:07,720
their very own angel
who fell from the stars.

592
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:17,680
AMY: Every time we flew away
with the Doctor,

593
00:43:17,760 --> 00:43:19,960
-we'd just become part of his life.
-Come with me.

594
00:43:20,040 --> 00:43:22,640
But he never stood still long enough
to become part of ours.

595
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:24,960
-(TYRES SQUEALING)
-Except once.

596
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:27,760
-Haven't you see them?
-AMY: The year of the slow invasion.

597
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:30,760
I've recommended we treat this
as a hostile incursion.

598
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:34,240
There are soldiers all over my house
and I'm in my pants.

599
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:38,320
We have two lives,
real life and Doctor life.

600
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:42,200
Our best hope now is each other.

601
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:45,120
-What do we do?
-Choose?

